  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-8 clean bounded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors scoped-out (acceptable at MRL 2). Operating envelope explicitly bounded: flow rate 1–7 L/min, rotational speed 1500–3500 RPM, inlet pressure 5–20 mmHg, outlet pressure 60–120 mmHg, blood temperature 20–37 °C. Applicability constrained to adult patients, non-pulsatile CPB, and pump geometries within ±0.15 mm dimensional tolerance of the FDA generic design. Validation dataset covers 4 of 5 declared flow-speed combinations; sparse coverage at the 1 L/min / 3500 RPM corner is documented as a coverage gap with conservative uncertainty inflation.",
