    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb/operating-envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "CPB hemolysis CFD operating envelope — bounded flow and speed ranges",
      "description": "Explicit quantitative bounds within which the CFD model is declared applicable: blood flow rate 1–7 L/min (five discrete operating points: 1, 2, 3, 5, 7 L/min); impeller rotational speed 1500–3500 RPM (five discrete levels: 1500, 2000, 2500, 3000, 3500 RPM); inlet gauge pressure 5–20 mmHg; outlet gauge pressure 60–120 mmHg; blood temperature 20–37 °C; hematocrit 35–45 %. Pump geometry bounded to ±0.15 mm dimensional tolerance on all wetted surfaces relative to the FDA generic centrifugal pump nominal geometry. Claims made outside these bounds are explicitly out of scope."
    },
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Adult non-pulsatile CPB applicability constraint",
      "description": "Model applicability is constrained to: (1) adult patients (body surface area 1.5–2.2 m², cardiac output demand 3–7 L/min); (2) non-pulsatile CPB mode only — pulsatile assist and LVAD duty cycles are excluded; (3) FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry family with wetted-surface dimensional deviations no greater than ±0.15 mm from nominal; (4) Newtonian blood rheology approximation valid for shear rates above 100 s⁻¹ as confirmed by sensitivity analysis; (5) single-phase flow — cavitation and two-phase regimes are out of scope. Results must not be extrapolated to pediatric patients, pulsatile devices, or geometries outside the stated tolerance band."
    }
  },
